@startuml
title Viaverse Category / Taxonomy / Dynamic Environment — Use Case Diagram
left to right direction

actor User
actor "Worker / Business" as Worker
actor "Admin / Content Ops" as Admin
actor "Search / Matching" as Search
actor Localization
actor "Analytics / AI" as Analytics

rectangle "Taxonomy / Dynamic Environment Boundary" {
  usecase "Configure dynamic environment\narea + interests" as Env
  usecase "Browse category tree" as Category
  usecase "Select tags / intents" as Tags
  usecase "Personalized feed filters" as Feed
  usecase "Create request with category\nbudget + urgency" as Post
  usecase "Map provider capabilities\ncategories + service area" as Offer
  usecase "Match request to providers" as Match
  usecase "Rank by relevance\ntrust + distance + availability" as Rank
  usecase "Manage taxonomy\ncategory/tag/forms" as AdminTax
  usecase "Manage category rules\nfields/fees/risk" as Rules
  usecase "Localize category labels\nTR/EN slugs" as Local
  usecase "Publish taxonomy version" as Publish
  usecase "Analyze taxonomy quality" as Quality
  usecase "AI category suggestion" as AI
  usecase "Emit events\nTaxonomyPublished\nCategoryMapped" as Events
}

User --> Env
Env --> Category
Category --> Tags
Tags --> Feed
User --> Post
Worker --> Offer
Post --> Match
Offer --> Match
Match --> Rank
Admin --> AdminTax
AdminTax --> Rules
Rules --> Local
Local --> Publish
Publish --> Quality
Quality --> AI
AI --> Events
Search --> Match
Localization --> Local
Analytics --> AI

note bottom
"Dinamik çevre" fixed neighborhood değildir.
Kullanıcı kendi area, interest, category ve intent sinyallerine göre
feed/search/matching kapsamını belirler.
end note
@enduml
